contentrichtext.text: '''Phinehas''', '''Pinhas''', or '''Pinchas''' may refer to: ==Biblical figures== *[[Phinehas]], son of Eleazar and grandson of Aaron the High Priest *[[Hophni and Phinehas|Phinehas]], son of the High Priest Eli; he was a priest at Shiloh, and died when the Philistines captured the Ark of the Covenant ==Rabbis== *[[Phinehas ben Jair]], an early Jewish rabbi of the 2nd century ==Musicians== *[[Pinchas Zukerman]], a noted Israeli violinist, violist, and conductor ==Writers== *[[Pinchas Sadeh]] (1929-94), Polish-born Israeli novelist and poet ==Sports people== *[[Pinhas Gershon]], Israeli basketball coach ==Politicians== *[[Pinchas Sapir]] (1906â€“75), Israeli politician ==Other == *[[Pinchas (parsha)]], the 41st weekly Torah portion *[[Phineas Priesthood]], a Christian Identity movement == See also == * [[Phineas (disambiguation)]] (a different name) {{disambig}}
